{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Today I'm going to take you on a voyage"},{"time":3000,"text":"to some place so deep,"},{"time":5000,"text":"so dark, so unexplored"},{"time":8000,"text":"that we know less about it than we know about the dark side of the moon."},{"time":11000,"text":"It's a place of myth and legend."},{"time":13000,"text":"It's a place marked on ancient maps"},{"time":15000,"text":"as \"here be monsters.\""},{"time":18000,"text":"It is a place where each new voyage of exploration"},{"time":21000,"text":"brings back new discoveries of creatures so wondrous and strange"},{"time":24000,"text":"that our forefathers would have considered them monstrous indeed."},{"time":27000,"text":"Instead, they just make me green with envy"},{"time":29000,"text":"that my colleague from IUCN"},{"time":31000,"text":"was able to go on this journey to the south of Madagascar seamounts"},{"time":34000,"text":"to actually take photographs"},{"time":36000,"text":"and to see these wondrous creatures of the deep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"We are talking about the high seas."},{"time":42000,"text":"The \"high seas\" is a legal term,"},{"time":44000,"text":"but in fact, it covers 50 percent of the planet."},{"time":47000,"text":"With an average depth of the oceans"},{"time":49000,"text":"of 4,000 meters,"},{"time":51000,"text":"in fact, the high seas covers and provides"},{"time":54000,"text":"nearly 90 percent of the habitat"},{"time":57000,"text":"for life on this Earth."},{"time":60000,"text":"It is, in theory, the global commons,"},{"time":62000,"text":"belonging to us all."},{"time":64000,"text":"But in reality,"},{"time":66000,"text":"it is managed by and for"},{"time":68000,"text":"those who have the resources"},{"time":70000,"text":"to go out and exploit it."},{"time":73000,"text":"So today I'm going to take you on a voyage"},{"time":75000,"text":"to cast light on some of the outdated myths"},{"time":77000,"text":"and legends and assumptions"},{"time":79000,"text":"that have kept us as the true stakeholders"},{"time":82000,"text":"in the high seas in the dark."},{"time":84000,"text":"We're going to voyage to some of these special places"},{"time":87000,"text":"that we've been discovering in the past few years"},{"time":89000,"text":"to show why we really need to care."},{"time":92000,"text":"And then finally, we're going to try"},{"time":94000,"text":"to develop and pioneer a new perspective"},{"time":96000,"text":"on high seas governance"},{"time":98000,"text":"that's rooted in ocean-basin-wide conservation,"},{"time":101000,"text":"but framed in an arena of global norms"},{"time":104000,"text":"of precaution and respect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"So here is a picture of the high seas"},{"time":109000,"text":"as seen from above --"},{"time":111000,"text":"that area in the darker blue."},{"time":113000,"text":"To me, as an international lawyer,"},{"time":115000,"text":"this scared me far more"},{"time":117000,"text":"than any of the creatures or the monsters we may have seen,"},{"time":119000,"text":"for it belies the notion that you can actually protect the ocean,"},{"time":122000,"text":"the global ocean,"},{"time":124000,"text":"that provides us all with carbon storage,"},{"time":126000,"text":"with heat storage, with oxygen,"},{"time":129000,"text":"if you can only protect 36 percent."},{"time":133000,"text":"This is indeed the true heart of the planet."},{"time":137000,"text":"Some of the problems that we have to confront"},{"time":139000,"text":"are that the current international laws --"},{"time":141000,"text":"for example, shipping --"},{"time":143000,"text":"provide more protection"},{"time":145000,"text":"to the areas closest to shore."},{"time":147000,"text":"For example, garbage discharge,"},{"time":149000,"text":"something you would think just simply goes away,"},{"time":151000,"text":"but the laws regulating"},{"time":153000,"text":"ship discharge of garbage"},{"time":155000,"text":"actually get weaker the further you are from shore."},{"time":158000,"text":"As a result, we have garbage patches"},{"time":161000,"text":"the size of twice-Texas."},{"time":164000,"text":"It's unbelievable."},{"time":166000,"text":"We used to think the solution to pollution"},{"time":169000,"text":"was dilution,"},{"time":171000,"text":"but that has proved to be no longer the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"So what we have learned from social scientists"},{"time":177000,"text":"and economists like Elinor Ostrom,"},{"time":179000,"text":"who are studying the phenomenon"},{"time":181000,"text":"of management of the commons on a local scale,"},{"time":183000,"text":"is that there are certain prerequisites"},{"time":186000,"text":"that you can put into place"},{"time":188000,"text":"that enable you to manage"},{"time":190000,"text":"and access open space"},{"time":193000,"text":"for the good of one and all."},{"time":196000,"text":"And these include a sense of shared responsibility,"},{"time":199000,"text":"common norms that bind people together as a community."},{"time":202000,"text":"Conditional access: You can invite people in,"},{"time":205000,"text":"but they have to be able to play by the rules."},{"time":208000,"text":"And of course, if you want people to play by the rules,"},{"time":210000,"text":"you still need an effective system"},{"time":212000,"text":"of monitoring and enforcement,"},{"time":214000,"text":"for as we've discovered,"},{"time":216000,"text":"you can trust, but you also need to verify."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"What I'd also like to convey"},{"time":220000,"text":"is that it is not all doom and gloom"},{"time":222000,"text":"that we are seeing in the high seas."},{"time":224000,"text":"For a group of very dedicated individuals --"},{"time":227000,"text":"scientists, conservationists,"},{"time":229000,"text":"photographers and states --"},{"time":232000,"text":"were able to actually change a tragic trajectory"},{"time":235000,"text":"that was destroying fragile seascapes"},{"time":237000,"text":"such as this coral garden"},{"time":239000,"text":"that you see in front of you."},{"time":241000,"text":"That is, we're able to save it from a fate"},{"time":243000,"text":"of deep-sea bottom trawling."},{"time":245000,"text":"And how did we do that?"},{"time":247000,"text":"Well, as I said, we had a group of photographers that went out on board ships"},{"time":250000,"text":"and actually photographed the activities in process."},{"time":253000,"text":"But we also spent many hours"},{"time":255000,"text":"in the basements of the United Nations,"},{"time":257000,"text":"trying to work with governments to make them understand"},{"time":260000,"text":"what was going on so far away from land"},{"time":262000,"text":"that few of us had ever even imagined"},{"time":264000,"text":"that these creatures existed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"So within three years,"},{"time":268000,"text":"from 2003 to 2006,"},{"time":271000,"text":"we were able to get norm in place"},{"time":273000,"text":"that actually changed the paradigm"},{"time":275000,"text":"of how fishers went about"},{"time":277000,"text":"deep-sea bottom trawling."},{"time":279000,"text":"Instead of \"go anywhere, do anything you want,\""},{"time":282000,"text":"we actually created a regime"},{"time":284000,"text":"that required prior assessment of where you're going"},{"time":287000,"text":"and a duty to prevent significant harm."},{"time":290000,"text":"In 2009, when the U.N. reviewed progress,"},{"time":293000,"text":"they discovered"},{"time":295000,"text":"that almost 100 million square-kilometers of seabed"},{"time":298000,"text":"had been protected."},{"time":300000,"text":"This does not mean that it's the final solution,"},{"time":302000,"text":"or that this even provides permanent protection."},{"time":304000,"text":"But what it does mean"},{"time":306000,"text":"is that a group of individuals can form a community"},{"time":309000,"text":"to actually shape"},{"time":311000,"text":"the way high seas are governed,"},{"time":313000,"text":"to create a new regime."},{"time":315000,"text":"So I'm looking optimistically at our opportunities"},{"time":318000,"text":"for creating a true, blue perspective"},{"time":321000,"text":"for this beautiful planet."},{"time":323000,"text":"Sylvia's wish"},{"time":325000,"text":"provides us with that leverage, that access"},{"time":328000,"text":"to the heart of human beings,"},{"time":330000,"text":"you might say,"},{"time":332000,"text":"who have rarely seen places beyond their own toes,"},{"time":335000,"text":"but are now hopefully going to become interested"},{"time":338000,"text":"in the full life-cycle of creatures like these sea turtles,"},{"time":341000,"text":"who indeed spend most of their time in the high seas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"Today, we're just going to voyage to a small sampling"},{"time":348000,"text":"of some of these special areas,"},{"time":350000,"text":"just to give you an idea of the flavor"},{"time":352000,"text":"of the riches and wonders they do contain."},{"time":355000,"text":"The Sargasso Sea, for example,"},{"time":357000,"text":"is not a sea bounded by coastlines,"},{"time":359000,"text":"but it is bounded by oceanic currents"},{"time":362000,"text":"that contain and envelope"},{"time":364000,"text":"this wealth of sargassum"},{"time":366000,"text":"that grows and aggregates there."},{"time":368000,"text":"It's also known as the spawning ground for eels"},{"time":372000,"text":"from Northern European"},{"time":374000,"text":"and Northern American rivers"},{"time":376000,"text":"that are now so dwindling in numbers"},{"time":378000,"text":"that they've actually stopped showing up in Stockholm,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and five showed up in the U.K. just recently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"But the Sargasso Sea,"},{"time":385000,"text":"the same way it aggregates sargassum weed,"},{"time":388000,"text":"actually is pulling in the plastic"},{"time":390000,"text":"from throughout the region."},{"time":392000,"text":"This picture doesn't exactly show"},{"time":394000,"text":"the plastics that I would like it to show, because I haven't been out there myself."},{"time":397000,"text":"But there has just been a study"},{"time":399000,"text":"that was released in February"},{"time":401000,"text":"that showed there are 200,000"},{"time":403000,"text":"pieces of plastic per square-kilometer"},{"time":406000,"text":"now floating in the surface of the Sargasso Sea,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and that is affecting the habitat"},{"time":411000,"text":"for the many species in their juvenile stages"},{"time":414000,"text":"who come to the Sargasso Sea"},{"time":416000,"text":"for its protection and its food."},{"time":419000,"text":"The Sargasso Sea is also a wondrous place"},{"time":422000,"text":"for the aggregation of these unique species"},{"time":424000,"text":"that have developed to mimic the sargassum habitat."},{"time":427000,"text":"It also provides a special habitat"},{"time":429000,"text":"for these flying fish to lay their eggs."},{"time":433000,"text":"But what I'd like to get from this picture"},{"time":435000,"text":"is that we truly do have an opportunity"},{"time":437000,"text":"to launch a global initiative for protection."},{"time":440000,"text":"Thus, the government of Bermuda has recognized the need"},{"time":443000,"text":"and its responsibility"},{"time":445000,"text":"as having some of the Sargasso Sea"},{"time":447000,"text":"within its national jurisdiction --"},{"time":449000,"text":"but the vast majority is beyond --"},{"time":451000,"text":"to help spearhead a movement"},{"time":453000,"text":"to achieve protection for this vital area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Spinning down to someplace a little bit cooler than here right now:"},{"time":458000,"text":"the Ross Sea in the Southern Ocean."},{"time":460000,"text":"It's actually a bay."},{"time":462000,"text":"It's considered high seas, because the continent"},{"time":464000,"text":"has been put off limits"},{"time":466000,"text":"to territorial claims."},{"time":468000,"text":"So anything in the water is treated as if it's the high seas."},{"time":471000,"text":"But what makes the Ross Sea important"},{"time":473000,"text":"is the vast sea of pack ice"},{"time":476000,"text":"that in the spring and summer"},{"time":478000,"text":"provides a wealth of phytoplankton and krill"},{"time":480000,"text":"that supports what, till recently,"},{"time":482000,"text":"has been a virtually intact"},{"time":484000,"text":"near-shore ecosystem."},{"time":487000,"text":"But unfortunately, CCAMLR,"},{"time":489000,"text":"the regional commission"},{"time":491000,"text":"in charge of conserving and managing fish stocks"},{"time":493000,"text":"and other living marine resources,"},{"time":495000,"text":"is unfortunately starting to give in to fishing interests"},{"time":498000,"text":"and has authorized the expansion"},{"time":500000,"text":"of toothfish fisheries in the region."},{"time":503000,"text":"The captain of a New Zealand vessel"},{"time":505000,"text":"who was just down there"},{"time":507000,"text":"is reporting a significant decline"},{"time":509000,"text":"in the number of the Ross Sea killer whales,"},{"time":512000,"text":"who are directly dependent on the Antarctic toothfish"},{"time":514000,"text":"as their main source of food."},{"time":517000,"text":"So what we need to do is to stand up boldly,"},{"time":520000,"text":"singly and together,"},{"time":522000,"text":"to push governments,"},{"time":524000,"text":"to push regional fisheries management organizations,"},{"time":526000,"text":"to declare our right"},{"time":528000,"text":"to declare certain areas off-limits to high seas fishing,"},{"time":531000,"text":"so that the freedom to fish no longer means"},{"time":533000,"text":"the freedom to fish anywhere and anytime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"Coming closer to here, the Costa Rica Dome"},{"time":539000,"text":"is a recently discovered area --"},{"time":541000,"text":"potentially year-round habitat for blue whales."},{"time":543000,"text":"There's enough food there to last them"},{"time":545000,"text":"the summer and the winter long."},{"time":547000,"text":"But what's unusual about the Costa Rica Dome"},{"time":549000,"text":"is, in fact, it's not a permanent place."},{"time":551000,"text":"It's an oceanographic phenomenon"},{"time":553000,"text":"that shifts in time and space on a seasonal basis."},{"time":556000,"text":"So, in fact, it's not permanently in the high seas."},{"time":558000,"text":"It's not permanently in the exclusive economic zones"},{"time":561000,"text":"of these five Central American countries,"},{"time":563000,"text":"but it moves with the season."},{"time":566000,"text":"As such, it does create a challenge to protect,"},{"time":569000,"text":"but we also have a challenge protecting the species that move along with it."},{"time":572000,"text":"We can use the same technologies that fishers use"},{"time":575000,"text":"to identify where the species are,"},{"time":577000,"text":"in order to close the area"},{"time":579000,"text":"when it's most vulnerable,"},{"time":581000,"text":"which may, in some cases, be year-round."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Getting closer to shore, where we are,"},{"time":586000,"text":"this was in fact taken in the Galapagos."},{"time":588000,"text":"Many species are headed through this region,"},{"time":590000,"text":"which is why there's been so much attention"},{"time":592000,"text":"put into conservation"},{"time":594000,"text":"of the Eastern Tropical Pacific Seascape."},{"time":596000,"text":"This is the initiative that's been coordinated"},{"time":598000,"text":"by Conservation International"},{"time":600000,"text":"with a variety of partners and governments"},{"time":602000,"text":"to actually try to bring integrated management regime"},{"time":605000,"text":"throughout the area."},{"time":607000,"text":"That is, it provides a wonderful example of where you can go"},{"time":609000,"text":"with a real regional initiative."},{"time":611000,"text":"It's protecting five World Heritage sites."},{"time":614000,"text":"Unfortunately, the World Heritage Convention"},{"time":617000,"text":"does not recognize the need to protect areas"},{"time":620000,"text":"beyond national jurisdiction, at present."},{"time":623000,"text":"So a place like the Costa Rica Dome"},{"time":625000,"text":"could not technically qualify"},{"time":627000,"text":"the time it's in the high seas."},{"time":629000,"text":"So what we've been suggesting"},{"time":631000,"text":"is that we either need to amend the World Heritage Convention,"},{"time":634000,"text":"so that it can adopt"},{"time":637000,"text":"and urge universal protection of these World Heritage sites,"},{"time":640000,"text":"or we need to change the name"},{"time":642000,"text":"and call it Half-the-World Heritage Convention."},{"time":645000,"text":"But what we also know is that species like these sea turtles"},{"time":648000,"text":"do not stay put in the Eastern Tropical Pacific Seascape."},{"time":652000,"text":"These happen to go down to a vast South Pacific Gyre,"},{"time":655000,"text":"where they spend most of their time"},{"time":657000,"text":"and often end up getting hooked like this,"},{"time":659000,"text":"or as bycatch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"So what I'd really like to suggest is that we need to scale-up."},{"time":664000,"text":"We need to work locally,"},{"time":666000,"text":"but we also need to work ocean-basin-wide."},{"time":669000,"text":"We have the tools and technologies now"},{"time":672000,"text":"to enable us to take a broader"},{"time":674000,"text":"ocean-basin-wide initiative."},{"time":676000,"text":"We've heard about the Tagging of Pacific Predators project,"},{"time":679000,"text":"one of the 17 Census of Marine Life projects."},{"time":682000,"text":"It's provided us data like this,"},{"time":684000,"text":"of tiny, little sooty shearwaters"},{"time":687000,"text":"that make the entire ocean basin their home."},{"time":689000,"text":"They fly 65,000 kilometers"},{"time":691000,"text":"in less than a year."},{"time":693000,"text":"So we have the tools and treasures coming from the Census of Marine Life."},{"time":696000,"text":"And its culminating year"},{"time":698000,"text":"that's going to be launched in October."},{"time":700000,"text":"So stay tuned for further information."},{"time":702000,"text":"What I find so exciting"},{"time":704000,"text":"is that the Census of Marine Life"},{"time":706000,"text":"has looked at more than the tagging of pacific predators;"},{"time":709000,"text":"it's also looked in the really unexplored mid-water column,"},{"time":712000,"text":"where creatures like this flying sea cucumber"},{"time":714000,"text":"have been found."},{"time":716000,"text":"And fortunately, we've been able, as IUCN,"},{"time":719000,"text":"to team up with the Census of Marine Life"},{"time":721000,"text":"and many of the scientists working there"},{"time":723000,"text":"to actually try to translate"},{"time":725000,"text":"much of this information to policymakers."},{"time":727000,"text":"We have the support of governments now behind us."},{"time":730000,"text":"We've been revealing this information through technical workshops."},{"time":733000,"text":"And the exciting thing is that we do have sufficient information"},{"time":736000,"text":"to move ahead to protect some of these"},{"time":738000,"text":"significant hope spots, hotspots."},{"time":741000,"text":"At the same time we're saying,"},{"time":743000,"text":"\"Yes, we need more. We need to move forward.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"But many of you have said,"},{"time":747000,"text":"if you get these marine protected areas,"},{"time":749000,"text":"or a reasonable regime for high seas fisheries management in place,"},{"time":752000,"text":"how are you going to enforce it?"},{"time":754000,"text":"Which leads me to my second passion besides ocean science,"},{"time":757000,"text":"which is outer space technology."},{"time":759000,"text":"I wanted to be an astronaut,"},{"time":761000,"text":"so I've constantly followed"},{"time":763000,"text":"what are the tools available to monitor Earth"},{"time":765000,"text":"from outer space --"},{"time":767000,"text":"and that we have incredible tools like we've been learning about,"},{"time":770000,"text":"in terms of being able to follow tagged species"},{"time":772000,"text":"throughout their life-cycles"},{"time":774000,"text":"in the open ocean."},{"time":776000,"text":"We can also tag and track fishing vessels."},{"time":779000,"text":"Many already have transponders on board"},{"time":782000,"text":"that allow us to find out where they are and even what they're doing."},{"time":785000,"text":"But not all the vessels have those to date."},{"time":787000,"text":"It does not take too much rocket science"},{"time":790000,"text":"to actually try to create new laws to mandate,"},{"time":793000,"text":"if you're going to have the privilege"},{"time":795000,"text":"of accessing our high seas resources,"},{"time":798000,"text":"we need to know -- someone needs to know --"},{"time":800000,"text":"where you are and what you're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"So it brings me to my main take-home message,"},{"time":805000,"text":"which is we can avert a tragedy of the commons."},{"time":808000,"text":"We can stop the collision course"},{"time":810000,"text":"of 50 percent of the planet"},{"time":812000,"text":"with the high seas."},{"time":814000,"text":"But we need to think broad-scale. We need to think globally."},{"time":817000,"text":"We need to change how we actually go about"},{"time":819000,"text":"managing these resources."},{"time":822000,"text":"We need to get the new paradigm"},{"time":824000,"text":"of precaution and respect."},{"time":826000,"text":"At the same time, we need to think locally,"},{"time":828000,"text":"which is the joy and marvel of Sylvia's hope spot wish,"},{"time":831000,"text":"is that we can shine a spotlight"},{"time":833000,"text":"on many of these previously unknown areas,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and to bring people to the table, if you will,"},{"time":839000,"text":"to actually make them feel part of this community"},{"time":842000,"text":"that truly has a stake"},{"time":844000,"text":"in their future management."},{"time":846000,"text":"And third is that we need to look at ocean-basin-wide management."},{"time":849000,"text":"Our species are ocean-basin-wide."},{"time":852000,"text":"Many of the deep-sea communities"},{"time":855000,"text":"have genetic distribution"},{"time":857000,"text":"that goes ocean-basin-wide."},{"time":859000,"text":"We need to better understand,"},{"time":861000,"text":"but we also need to start to manage and protect."},{"time":864000,"text":"And in order to do that,"},{"time":866000,"text":"you also need ocean-basin management regimes."},{"time":868000,"text":"That is, we have regional management regimes"},{"time":871000,"text":"within the exclusive economic zone,"},{"time":873000,"text":"but we need to scale these up, we need to build their capacity,"},{"time":876000,"text":"so they're like the Southern Ocean,"},{"time":878000,"text":"where they do have the two-pronged fisheries"},{"time":880000,"text":"and conservation organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"So with that, I would just like to sincerely thank and honor"},{"time":886000,"text":"Sylvia Earle for her wish,"},{"time":888000,"text":"for it is helping us to put a face on the high seas"},{"time":890000,"text":"and the deep seas beyond national jurisdiction."},{"time":893000,"text":"It's helping to bring an incredible group"},{"time":895000,"text":"of talented people together"},{"time":897000,"text":"to really try to solve and penetrate"},{"time":899000,"text":"these problems that have created our obstacles"},{"time":902000,"text":"to management and rational use"},{"time":905000,"text":"of this area that was once so far away and remote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"So on this tour, I hope I provided you"},{"time":912000,"text":"with a new perspective of the high seas:"},{"time":914000,"text":"one, that it is our home too,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and that we need to work together"},{"time":919000,"text":"if we are to make this a sustainable ocean future for us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}